history.content: You will be on the waitlist until adjustment if you declare over the summer. Declarations won't be processed before the adjustment period starts, so you will be added from the waitlist. I wouldn't worry if I were you, there's a very high probability you will be in 170 in the fall.

Hello, I was enrolling for classes and I saw that I got put on the waitlist for CS170. From my understanding, I think that I am being put on the list because, even though I am intended to major in CS, I am still considered undeclared. Is there a possibility of me joining CS170 despite being undeclared? By the time the class starts however, I should be declared since I am going to take CS70 over the summer. The likelihood of me being unable to declare is very slim in my opinion, but still a possibility. How should I approach this? I really want to take CS170 in Fall 2021, but am meeting dead ends with how to do so.

For context, I have taken CS61A, am currently taking CS61B, and will take CS70 over the summer.
history.subject: Enrolling in CS170 but Waitlist is Hefty. Declaring by Summer
